@CoachLocks @njeremiduru @lilabbromberg @YahooSports @UofMaryland @President_Pines @Evans_TerpsAD What can fans do to promote diversity in coaching positions?

"If fans are willing, then talk with your feet... If fans aren't interested in supporting a team, the team will do what it can to keep them happy. The question is how fans can get organized," @njeremiduru says.

@CoachLocks @njeremiduru @lilabbromberg @YahooSports @UofMaryland @President_Pines @Evans_TerpsAD "It's definitely discouraging when you look around and see the same issues I was dealing with when I got started," @CoachLocks says. "But as coaches, we're taught to keep fighting the fight until there's no time left on the clock."

@CoachLocks @njeremiduru @lilabbromberg @YahooSports @UofMaryland @President_Pines @Evans_TerpsAD What is the next step in promoting diversity in coach hiring? "Let these owners, or in the case of college athletics these universities, understand that they are helping themselves by thinking about diversity in hiring," @njeremiduru says. "Doing the right thing also helps them."

@CoachLocks @njeremiduru @lilabbromberg @YahooSports @UofMaryland @President_Pines @Evans_TerpsAD Our panelists are pointing out flaws of the NFL's Rooney Rule, a policy implemented to encourage diversity in coaching.

"There's got to be something more, if we're going to get this turned around, than what exists systemically right now," @njeremiduru says.

@CoachLocks @njeremiduru @lilabbromberg @YahooSports As @lilabbromberg's story highlights, this summer @UofMaryland became the first and only FBS school with an African American president in @President_Pines, athletic director in @Evans_TerpsAD and head football coach in @CoachLocks.
